OL,3,CWATCH: 10mph danger driver handed
OL,4,Cprison sentence
OL,6,FThe court heard that in late February
OL,7,Fthis year, Lowrey had been jailed for
OL,8,F16 months by a judge for offending
OL,9,Fwhich included making a threat to kill
OL,10,Fa man while holding scissors to his
OL,11,Fthroat.
OL,13,FLowrey's barrister told how he had
OL,14,Fgone "out of control" and begun using
OL,15,Falcohol to cope after his father was
OL,16,Fhanded a lengthy jail term in 2023.
